NOTE ON LICENSE CHOICE:

This repository is currently documentation-only (Markdown, JSON, CSV
examples). CC BY 4.0 is the appropriate license for documentation and
written content.

If you later add substantial runnable code (for example, a FastAPI service),
consider adding an MIT License in a separate LICENSE-CODE file, or switching
the repository to MIT, so the code carries a standard software license.
MIT is the conventional choice for open-source code and is permissive and
widely understood.
